               <head>Kalim and Qudsi, divans</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh98002075 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85109396 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh89003718">
                  <summary>Early collection of dīvāns by two of the most important poets at Shahjahan's court in neat nastaʿlīq</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh89005046 http://lccn.loc.gov/n94035013" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4391-item1">
                     <locus from="1" to="69">ff. 1-69</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Collection of qaṣāʾid, ghazalīyāt, rubāʿīyāt, tarjīʿbands, and other brief mas̲navīyāt by one of the most important poets at the court of the Timurid or Mughal Emperor Shāh Jahān I, Abū Ṭālib Hamadānī Kāshānī, sometimes referred to as Ṭālibā-yi Kalīm. The poet was later commissioned to write a versified account of the reign, titled <title>Pādshāh'nāmah</title>, based on, though not limited to, approved prose accounts (especially that by Shaykh ʿAbd al-Ḥamīd Lāhawrī), also titled <title>Pādshāh'nāmah</title>, left incomplete on the poet's death in 1062/1652
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_128">Dīvān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_128">ديوان</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="viaf_53111694">Kalīm, Abū Ṭālib</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="viaf_53111694">كليم، ابو طالب</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh89005046" n="2" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4391-item2">
                     <locus from="70" to="171">ff. 70-171</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f3404">Ḥājjī Muḥammad Jān Mashhadī "Qudsī"</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_f3404">حاجى محمّد جان مشهدى قدسى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_296">Dīvān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_296">ديوان</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Collection of numerous qaṣāʾid, and a smaller quantity of ghazalīyāt, followed by rubāʿīyāt, by the premier poet at the court of the Timurid or Mughal Emperor Shāh Jahān I, Ḥājjī Muḥammad Jān Mashhadī "Qudsī". The poet was the first to be commissioned to write a versified account of the reign, titled <title>Pādshāh'nāmah</title>, based on, though not limited to, approved prose accounts (by, initially, Muḥammad Amīn Qazvīnī and later Shaykh ʿAbd al-Ḥamīd Lāhawrī), also titled <title>Pādshāh'nāmah</title>, left incomplete on the poet's death in 1056/1646 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated: 9 Muḥarram 1073/1662</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
